WEBVTT

00:03.234 --> 00:12.285
Great and peace to you from God our Father and our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ, our text for today is the Psalm that is appointed for this day, Psalm 24.

00:14.568 --> 00:25.341
The earth is the Lord's and the fullness thereof, the world and those who dwell therein, for he has founded it upon the seas and established it upon the rivers.

00:26.443 --> 00:29.106
Who shall ascend the hill of the Lord?

00:29.887 --> 00:32.530
And who shall stand in the holy place?

00:33.538 --> 00:41.947
He who has clean hands and a pure heart, who does not lift up his soul to what is false and does not swear deceitfully.

00:41.987 --> 00:48.194
He will receive blessing from the Lord and righteousness from the God of his salvation.

00:48.234 --> 00:54.801
Such is the generation of those who seek him, who seek the face of the God of Jacob.

00:55.742 --> 01:00.747
Lift up your heads, O Gaison, be lifted up, O ancient doors that the King of glory may come in.

01:00.787 --> 01:03.410
Who is this King of glory?

01:03.906 --> 01:06.610
The Lord, strong and mighty.

01:06.630 --> 01:09.534
The Lord, mighty and battle.

01:09.554 --> 01:15.182
Lift up your heads, O gates, and lift them up, O ancient doors, that the King of glory may come in.

01:16.123 --> 01:17.505
Who is this King of glory?

01:18.307 --> 01:19.228
The Lord of hosts.

01:20.089 --> 01:22.052
He is the King of glory.

01:22.793 --> 01:23.694
This is our text.

01:31.225 --> 01:31.986
Or over in Him.

01:32.738 --> 01:42.591
Based on this very psalm, lift up your heads, o ye mighty gates behold, the King of glory waits, the King of kings is drawing near.

01:42.651 --> 01:46.076
The Savior of the world is here.

01:47.197 --> 01:57.151
Just a few moments ago Pastor Mike talked about getting ready and preparing, and that's what we've been talking about all Adventist season, getting ready, ready to celebrate the birth of Christ.

01:58.412 --> 02:02.738
And as we do so, I want to take a brief look this morning at this psalm and

02:02.882 --> 02:04.645
and our preparation.

02:06.007 --> 02:13.439
Our preparation began hearing John the Baptist a couple of Sundays ago calling out repent for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.

02:14.601 --> 02:19.889
So that our preparation, our continual preparation is a life of repentance.

02:22.193 --> 02:30.226
Preparing, we come, we are all excited about Christmas and we should because it's a fulfillment of God's promise.

02:30.850 --> 02:38.341
that he may long ago through the prophet Isaiah, as we heard, as he foretold to Joseph in our gospel reading for today.

02:40.765 --> 02:43.248
When we go to the manger, I have a question, though.

02:44.250 --> 02:45.552
What do we look to see?

02:45.572 --> 02:58.030
Of course, the natural answer, and the right answer is we go to see this newborn child, this baby that God has given to us, this God in the flesh.

02:59.352 --> 03:00.754
Wonder of wonders.

03:02.466 --> 03:12.457
But this morning, I would like to direct you to not only look backward, but to look at the present and the future as we look into that major as well.

03:18.283 --> 03:21.827
In my childhood, we played outdoors a lot.

03:21.907 --> 03:28.274
We didn't have computers and video games and cell phones to occupy us.

03:28.634 --> 03:32.338
We went out to Ohio, and we played a lot.

03:32.770 --> 03:45.167
When it was time for supper in our household, it was important because my dad, being a pastor, we had to eat so we could have our family meal and our devotions and clean up and everything.

03:45.187 --> 03:50.294
And then he could go to make calls or visit or go to meetings or whatever.

03:51.035 --> 03:52.877
So it was very precise.

03:52.917 --> 03:57.063
So when mom called us for supper to come in, we had to come in.

03:57.083 --> 04:00.547
And as we came into the back doors, there she was right there by the kitchen.

04:00.608 --> 04:02.450
That's where our back door was.

04:02.530 --> 04:06.495
in the kitchen and I should say, go wash your hands.

04:10.240 --> 04:12.923
And we had to always wash our hands before we ate.

04:13.885 --> 04:16.027
Maybe you remember something like that as well.

04:16.568 --> 04:20.112
Being told often to wash your hands before doing something.

04:20.573 --> 04:22.015
Clean hands are important.

04:22.035 --> 04:27.602
We didn't want to get our, eat our meal with 30 hands and make the house dirty and all of that as well.

04:28.386 --> 04:32.131
We know that the importance of cleanliness is well clean hands.

04:32.952 --> 04:48.411
If I'm going to, in the hospital to have a surgery, I'm so glad that the nurses and doctors take that time that they put in to scrub up and to make sure that their hands are very clean and then they put on sterile gloves on top of it.

04:49.032 --> 04:50.834
Cleanliness is important.

04:52.290 --> 04:59.138
And especially if we were going over to somebody's house, we wanted to make sure that, okay, everything was clean and, yep, check the hands there, clean too.

04:59.198 --> 05:03.082
Our Psalm talks a little bit about clean hands.

05:03.823 --> 05:05.845
Just a brief background on this Psalm.

05:05.885 --> 05:17.498
It probably was written when the ark that had been captured by the Philistines in a battle and then returned to the Israelites, but not to Jerusalem.

05:17.618 --> 05:21.522
It's now coming and it's being brought into the city of Jerusalem.

05:22.402 --> 05:28.831
And so this hymn of praise was being sung of praise to God for all of his creation, for all that he had done.

05:28.871 --> 05:32.056
And it asks a very important question here.

05:32.076 --> 05:39.326
It says, who shall send the hill of the Lord and who shall stand in his holy place?

05:40.788 --> 05:45.074
Who's worthy to go into up to Mount Zion?

05:46.338 --> 05:51.364
to come into God's presence for the ark represented the presence of God for the people.

05:51.665 --> 05:55.389
It was his physical sign for them that he was with them.

05:59.554 --> 06:00.736
And it gives us the answer.

06:02.538 --> 06:07.664
He who has a clean heart, a clean hands, and a pure heart.

06:12.450 --> 06:15.474
We like to think that we would be worthy to

06:15.746 --> 06:19.752
stand to send to that hill and to stand in this holy place.

06:20.574 --> 06:26.864
But right here is the crux of the problem because we don't have clean hands.

06:27.305 --> 06:29.328
I'm not talking about being physically clean.

06:30.850 --> 06:31.972
We don't have pure hearts.

06:33.615 --> 06:40.466
Our hands are dirty because they carry out the desires of our hearts, the desires that are sinful from our birth.

06:43.714 --> 06:50.662
We don't deserve to ascend the hill and to stand into the presence of God, the Holy One.

06:52.604 --> 06:58.952
And it goes on from there and it asks, again, it says, who is this King of Glories?

06:59.593 --> 07:01.034
You know, it said, lift up your heads.

07:02.256 --> 07:03.137
Lift up your heads.

07:04.398 --> 07:05.940
Give honor to the King.

07:07.242 --> 07:07.862
Give honor.

07:07.922 --> 07:08.723
Be joyful.

07:09.404 --> 07:11.026
God, the King is here.

07:11.618 --> 07:13.940
Who is this king of glory that answers three times?

07:14.020 --> 07:20.366
And it says, Yahweh, the Lord, strong and mighty, Yahweh, mighty in battle, Yahweh.

07:20.747 --> 07:22.488
He is the king of glory.

07:26.913 --> 07:41.106
So when we look at the manger and we see the child Jesus, I want you to see not just a baby, not just the God in the flesh is a little baby, but who he came as, he came as

07:41.410 --> 07:42.431
the king of glory.

07:44.333 --> 07:46.555
It's what the angels announced to the shepherds.

07:47.897 --> 08:02.652
So many of our hymns talk about this event, life-changing, world-changing event of God becoming flesh as the king coming into the world.

08:05.134 --> 08:08.978
He's the one who's worthy to stand in God's presence.

08:09.378 --> 08:14.184
He is the one who is worthy to ascend to that holy hill.

08:16.808 --> 08:18.090
But that's not what he did.

08:21.154 --> 08:22.275
He did something different.

08:25.360 --> 08:29.185
He ascended a hill okay, but it was not a holy hill.

08:30.366 --> 08:34.612
It wasn't Mount Zion that he ascended, he ascended Mount Calvary.

08:35.513 --> 08:39.058
And he did so with the, he who had the cleanest

08:39.202 --> 08:48.793
hands, the perfectly clean hands, and the perfectly pure heart purposely took on the filthiness that is ours.

08:50.535 --> 08:59.084
And he carried it with him up to that hill, not to sit on a throne, but to be nailed on a cross.

09:03.569 --> 09:07.634
And he did this so that you and I

09:08.706 --> 09:11.710
could have clean hands and pure hearts.

09:15.295 --> 09:35.743
And because he rose from the dead and showed his victory over all that sinful, that is ours as the world, we do have clean hands and pure hearts given to us in the waters of baptism as we are washed and cleansed by his blood as we come to his table.

09:36.183 --> 09:38.066
And as we come to his table,

09:38.594 --> 09:43.241
We are coming into the presence of the king to partake of his meal.

09:48.309 --> 09:55.299
Jesus came as the child of Bethlehem and as the king of glory at his birth.

09:56.341 --> 10:05.234
He comes to us continually as the king who wants to rule in our lives now and every day, every moment of every day.

10:06.050 --> 10:11.036
He wants us to be the most important thing to him because we are the most important to him.

10:14.200 --> 10:17.064
And he wants us to look forward to his coming again.

10:17.124 --> 10:35.186
That's why our life is a continual preparation of repentance to God, for we still have dirty hands and impure hearts that have been cleansed and sanctified by him who purified us.

10:36.546 --> 10:38.708
through the cross and the resurrection.

10:40.791 --> 10:52.723
And so we see that King as a baby, we see him as the King of our lives now, and we look forward to his coming again so that we can say with St. John, even so, come Lord Jesus.

10:54.365 --> 11:02.674
So the invitation for us by this psalm and this hymn is to come, come see the baby, come, see the King.

11:06.210 --> 11:10.376
Charles Wesley wrote one of our hymns that we, our advent hymns that we sing.

11:10.876 --> 11:14.721
And I think in verse two, he kind of sums this up for us very well.

11:16.724 --> 11:30.302
He says, second verse, born thy people to deliver, born a child and yet a king, born to reign in us forever.

11:31.163 --> 11:33.426
Now thy gracious kingdom bring,

11:33.666 --> 11:49.085
By thine own eternal spirit rule in all our hearts alone, by thine all sufficient merit, raise us to thy glorious throne.

11:51.428 --> 11:51.948
Rejoice.

11:53.430 --> 11:53.991
Rejoice.

11:56.494 --> 12:02.562
The King has come for you, for me, for us all.

12:02.582 --> 12:02.962
Come,

12:04.194 --> 12:07.182
See the King in Jesus' name.

12:08.445 --> 12:08.806
Amen.

12:13.338 --> 12:18.873
May the peace of God which surpasses all understanding keep your hearts and minds in Christ Jesus.

12:19.936 --> 12:20.818
Amen.

